Happy holidays from our crew to yours!

Besides finding out that our family’s flight got canceled and they will no longer be coming to visit for the week, we had a lovely Christmas.

It’s our 5 year wedding anniversary 💖 not sure how he pulled off this surreal sunset, but what a gift 😉

Love my husband, the family we’ve created and all the little moments we get to share in our home. For those who may not know, 5 years ago we got our family to think they were getting dressed up for pictures at sunset when really they were also attending our surprise wedding! It was fun! 

Link to the full video on Stories 💗

A little end of year reflective practice that has made a big impact. 

As you’re filling up your own pages, think about what you created or cultivated last year that felt connected. Maybe just giving yourself permission to play with your supplies and not overthink the outcome was something you did for yourself. Connecting with creativity as a habit is a great way to enrich your life and find enjoyment, purpose, and meaning. 

Connecting with this creative community is one of the biggest blessings this year. I know I wasn’t as consistent with filming and sharing but I am letting go of that expectation of myself, knowing that I will make it more of a priority next year. That’s a lesson for me, because I find so much joy in not just the making or crafting part, sharing videos or snippets of my life and connecting with you has always been a bright spot 💖 Thank you!!

Big fan of fresh starts ✨The top is in my new planner and the bottom is in the middle of a notebook from 2021.

Using your notebooks any way you choose is a radical act of self-care. If you want to revisit old notebooks and go completely out of order on the pages, I want to encourage you to do so. It might feel uncomfortable at first, but leaning into the idea that you have creative freedom and hold the power of doing what feels best for you. No rules except to have fun. Thanks to everyone from around the world who’s gotten the printable already - Germany, Sweden, UK, and Australia!

Creative journaling using some of the MAP Your Month printable. By setting aside time to be intentional and engage in a creative activity, such as painting, journaling, or anything that makes you feel uplifted, calm and happy, we can gain a deeper understanding of ourselves and what we truly want in life.

Love leaves its mark in unexpected ways. Missing my dad, I asked for a sign and found this heart-shaped leaf at my feet. Knowing he's still watching over us brings peace to my heart. 💛🍃

To those who are missing someone special, know that you are not alone. Grief is a difficult journey, but it helps to remember that our loved ones live on in our hearts and memories. Take a moment to check in with yourself and remember that your well-being should be a top priority 💙 Anyone else in need of this reminder today? 

It’s not always easy, but it is really essential. So go ahead, indulge in whatever your definition of self-care might be. Make art, make a mess, make time for what matters most, or simply make a cup of tea and enjoy some peace and quiet. Whatever it is that brings you joy and relaxation, embrace it fully and without guilt. Remember, self-care is not selfish. Your well-being is worth it, and a little fun never hurt anyone.

Also, if you’re curious, I spent way too much time trying to figure out how to make this animation the way I had envisioned it, and though it didn’t turn out perfectly, I enjoyed (most of) the process.

On my father’s first heavenly birthday, I cherish every life stage with gratitude.

Felt his presence immensely this morning while I was about to ride a horse for the 2nd time in my life. (The first time was when I was 7 and it was awful because I got covered in mosquito bites). I realized I was the only one in shorts. It reminded me of how my Papa would have handled it. I pictured it perfectly. Instead of panicking, his hand would smack right onto his forehead, while simultaneously shaking his head and then breaking out into a big smile and sigh. He likely would have said, “Oh Archie!” while at first trying to hold back laughing at himself (and failing).

You can see how it unfolded in Stories but spoiler alert: I ended up with the most amazing horse named Thor, the most peaceful ride, no bug bites and no chafing. Grateful.

Work in progress – here’s where I am currently 👇🏽

Let’s call this the “messy middle”. The somewhat tough part where things often feel confusing and hard. This project of the studio renovation has become a lot bigger (and much more costly) after the demo happened. It revealed that a lot more work needed to be done. JC kind of predicted it, but this challenging phase of trusting the process feels scary.  The messy middle is like this – full of obstacles and bumps along the way. However, if you trust and keep going, you’ll learn valuable lessons and find new solutions.

After some thought and some reframing (literally as you can see here with the wood), I have decided that the messy middle will show me the way forward to the “happy medium.” This feels like a place of harmony and balance where I will feel content and confident that it’s even better than the original plan was to begin with. 

Remember, going through the messy middle might be the way to reach your happy medium. Embrace the hard times, learn from them, and trust you’ll reach a better place. We are all works in progress, after all. Here’s to embracing the messy, abundant and imperfect path to get to the best possible outcome.

(Also, excited to share with you soon about where I will be working temporarily for at least the next 3 months while this comes together!)

This is 45 ☀️

Right before my birthday every year, I find myself in a reflective mood. Time seems to pass so quickly, and I often wonder if I've done enough, accomplished enough, or if I'm experiencing my own little version of some sort of crisis, this time one called “midlife”.

Instead of getting lost in those thoughts, I decided to channel my energies into something positive. I drafted a list of lessons I have learned (and continue to be reminded of) that may offer insight and wisdom to others.

These reflections are a gift, a way of sharing the collective wisdom that comes with the passage of time. Whether you seek clarity, perspective, or inspiration, may these lessons light your path. Let's make every year one of learning, laughter, and leaning into what we love. Which of these resonates with you? 

(These are also on the blog if you’d rather see a comprehensive list all in one place)

2. Finish in under 15 minutes.

It felt so great to create with some constraints. Sometimes it’s easier to make something when you have a limited amount of time, would you agree?

The sign was for my sold out brush lettering workshop @thesehandscollective - so grateful!

Also how cute is Honey in that last shot?!

Sometimes I have no idea what I’m doing. Yet somehow taking a little leap of faith and trusting in aligned action has always landed me where I need to be. 

Are you feeling a little lost too? Or are you feeling grounded and guided? Right now it seems I am meant to be in this little corner of creativity, dreaming up some colorful plans. Can’t wait to share 2 of the big projects I’ve been working on with you - all around connecting, creating, and community.

Where are you right now? How are you feeling and what are you seeking when it comes to connecting with your creativity? Would love to know!
